data.enText: the edge of a piece of cloth that has been folded over and sewn, especially on a piece of clothing
to take up the hem of a dress (= to make the dress shorter)
to make a hem on sth

data.text: = hum and haw at hum v.

data.chText: 包围，限制（某人 / 某事物）
data.enText: to surround sb/sth so that they cannot move or grow easily
The village is hemmed in on all sides by mountains.

data.chText: 她觉得受到他们那些琐碎的规章制度的束缚。
data.enText: She felt hemmed in by all their petty rules and regulations.

tr: the edge of a piece of cloth
especially the finished edge that has been doubled under and stitched down
example: the hem of her dress was stained
he stitched weights into the curtain's hem
it seeped along the hem of his jacket

tr: the utterance of a sound similar to clearing the throat
intended to get attention, express hesitancy, fill a pause, hide embarrassment, warn a friend, etc.
fold over and sew together to provide with a hem

value.def: A hem on something such as a piece of clothing is an edge that is folded over and stitched down to prevent threads coming loose. The hem of a skirt or dress is the bottom edge.
value.tran: （衣物等的）褶边，卷边;（裙子的）下摆

value.def: If you hem something, you form a hem along its edge.

example.ex: Turn under and hem the outer edges...
Each dress is hemmed and scrupulously checked for imperfections.
example.tran: 每条连衣裙都缝上了褶边，并经过严格的检查，不允许有任何瑕疵。
